## Hard Rules

### Do NOT

- Approve a system with critical requirement failures
- Ignore test failures
- Skip documentation review
- Overlook quality enforcement gaps

### Do NOT Claim

- System is ready if critical gaps exist
- Tests are sufficient if coverage is incomplete
- Quality is enforced if mechanisms are missing

## Quality Standards

An audit must be:

| Aspect | Requirement |
|--------|-------------|
| Thorough | All components reviewed |
| Objective | Based on evidence, not opinion |
| Actionable | Clear recommendations |
| Documented | Full audit trail |

